Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
enc_source_verbose_output(25.10)              enc_source_verbose_output(25.10)

Name
       enc_source_verbose_output

Syntax
       enc_source_verbose_output

       Type: enum

       Choices: debug, echo, echo_comments

       Default: echo

       Used to control the verbosity of  the source -verbose output.

              * If  you specify echo, the output will only include the command
                lines.

              * If you specify debug, the output will include file name,  line
                number,  and command. This option is used to debug problems in
                scripts.

              * If you specify echo_comments, the  output  will  include  com-
                mands, comments and empty lines

Examples
              * By  default, source -verbose prints only the real command line
                start with #:

              * With  set enc_source_verbose_output  echo_comments,  all  file
                contents,   including  comment  lines  and  empty  lines,  are
                printed. Comment lines start with # and  command  lines  start
                with @:

